common_issues.title: CLI Model Validation Error: Publisher Model Not Found
common_issues.description: Users encounter a "404 Publisher Model Not Found" error when using the CLI.  The error message indicates the specified model was not found or the project lacks access.  Users should verify the model version and project access rights.

related_issues.title: CLI: 1 validation error for Model
related_issues.text: CLI: 1 validation error for Model ### Checked for Existing Issues? - [ ] Yes, I have checked existing issues and cannot find one related to this. ### Software Desktop Application, Pieces CLI ### Operating System / Platform macOS ### Your Pieces OS Version PiecesOS 12.1.0 ### Early Access Program - [ ] Yes, this is related to an Early Access Program feature. ### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug. Error generating summary: 404 Publisher Model `projects/pi3c3s-cloud-server/locations/us-east1/publishers/google/models/gemini-pro` was not found or your project does not have access to it. Please ensure you are using a valid model version. For more information, see: https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/generative-ai/docs/learn/model-versions

recommendations: Prioritize resolving 'CLI Model Validation Error: Publisher Model Not Found' as it's the most frequent issue.
Update CLI documentation and error messages to guide users on verifying model version and project access.
Investigate and address the root cause of the '404 Publisher Model Not Found' error within the CLI.
Monitor the 'app:pieces cli' category for recurring issues and trends.
